post_text:
Dear West Park Friends, Family, Neighbors, and Scholars,

If you drive past West Park Academy, you will see four large banners attached to the front of the school proclaiming what we stand for. These values are ideals, goals, and inspirations to all who are a part of the school. But now, more than ever, these are values that must unite us against all things that suffocate our nation, our city, and even our community.

Those four values are: COMMUNITY, INTEGRITY, RESILIENCE, and EXCELLENCE. Sadly, we have witnessed our society fail to be a community where love and equality are cherished and held sacred. We have experienced an utter letdown of integral members of our society who have abused…

Parents - with only four weeks left to go, here are some tips to help and your scholars get through to the end of the academic year (May 21):

• Create a routine
o School and most jobs are about rhythm and routine. Try to keep each day of the week the same. This includes a set bedtime, mealtimes, waking up each morning, working and playing.

• Break it up
o Not everything has to be done at once. As you build your routine, take breaks along the way and “chunk” the work.

• Work together side-by-side
o If your job requires you to work from home, work together simultaneously. Sometimes being near someone else who is working increases work productivity and motivation. Plus, this serves as a…

Friends and family,

Our buildings are continuing to undergo intense cleaning to ensure that our campus is virus free. Unfortunately this means we have to suspend our office operations and meal program tomorrow. With next week being spring break please be sure to find other local schools who are offering this same program.

Continue to check our page daily for updates, Tiger Trivia and your teachers posting videos of them reading some of their favorite stories!!! You won’t want to miss it.

Please message us if you are in need of anything! Continue to stay safe and healthy!!

~Mr. Jaissle

post_text: Good morning families, we are continuing to monitor the coronavirus situation and make adjustments in the best interest of student and staff safety. To help prevent the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19), we are cancelling all scheduled field trips and prohibiting spectator participation at extra-curricular events. If you have specific questions about an event, feel free to call the school or email the front office. Thank you for your understanding. We will continue to post updates as they come.

post_text: On December 4th, West Park Academy inducted seven new members to the West Park Honor Society. The WPHS initiates qualifying students who meet rigorous academic, civic and leadership standards. Pictured are the seven newest members - Osborne, Jasmine, Izabella, Danny, Gabbi, Julien, and Nyla - as well as returning member, Adrian. Congratulations to all of our members! Special thanks to Mr. LaRiccia and Mrs. Wagner, our co-advisors this year.
